Additionally, during a recession, businesses may reduce their workforce and lay off employees to cut costs, which could lead to an increase in the unemployment rate. As the economy recovers and businesses start to expand again, they may begin hiring new employees, resulting in a decrease in the unemployment rate. It's important to note that other factors such as government policies, changes in monetary policy, international factors, and other economic indicators may also contribute to these variations.
